      "line": 50,
      "message": "Throws declaration should not be used in case of unchecked exception. Runtime exceptions can occur anywhere in a program, and adding throws declaration in every method would reduce a program's clarity. When user looks at \"throws Exception\" declaration he expects Checked Exception. If you really want to inform user about runtime exception, put @throws in javadoc.",
